race.comment: MAY BE BUBBLES (11) hasn't done a lot so far but will find this easier. Well fancied on debut when fair, the raced in a much richer maiden and was safely held. This easier, back in trip and blinkers added. Given another chance. PACIFIC CHILL (12) is a two-start maiden who returned last time and finished seventh at Cranbourne over 1000m, beaten 4 lengths. Will take a lot from that hit-out and looks a strong chance to break through. SUPERLIV (10) is a maiden galloper who hasn't raced since the winter. Has placed fresh and expecting a bold return. BRAZEN DIVA (4) placed fresh then missed the frame in a richer maiden at Pakenham. Capable of much better. ALPHABET (9) rates highly and expected to do much better second-up.
